         <component>
            <section ID="clinicalPharmacology">
               <id root="4d068db2-c4a8-4ca6-8c1d-3fde663dbdde"/>
               <code code="34090-1" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY SECTION"/>
               <title>CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Elliotts B Solution provides a buffered salt solution for use as a diluent for the intrathecal
administration of methotrexate sodium and cytarabine. It has been demonstrated
that Elliotts B Solution is comparable to cere­brospinal fluid in pH,
electrolyte composition, glucose content, and osmolarity:</paragraph>
                  <br/>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>Comparison of Electrolyte Composition, pH and Nonelectrolytic Constituents of Elliotts B Solution and CSF</paragraph>
                  <table ID="if9acbcd0-06db-4898-8bd5-c2a36488e99c" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="2">
                     <col width="150"/>
                     <col width="80" align="center"/>
                     <col width="70" align="center"/>
